# FreshLens — Git & GitHub Workflow

## Branching (GitHub Flow)

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Feature | `feat/<area>-<desc>` | `feat/api-scan-endpoint` |
| Fix | `fix/<area>-<desc>` | `fix/web-tenant-filter` |
| Docs | `docs/<topic>` | `docs/srs-architecture` |
| Chore | `chore/<topic>` | `chore/ci-lint` |

**Rules:** Never commit to `main` directly · One issue per branch · PR references issue (`Closes #N`) · PRs &lt; 400 lines · Squash merge after CI + 1 approval

## Commit format

```
feat(api): add POST /scan with 202 async response
fix(web): correct tenant filter on dashboard
chore(ci): add RLS isolation test
```

## When implementing a feature

1. Find or create a GitHub Issue with acceptance criteria
2. Branch from `main`: `feat/<area>-<desc>`
3. Implement only in the correct monorepo path
4. Open PR using `.github/pull_request_template.md`
5. Request review from area owner (see CODEOWNERS)
6. Merge when CI green + approved

## Milestones (CS3203)

| Milestone | Due | Focus |
|-----------|-----|-------|
| M1 | Jul 12 | Proposal, feasibility, schedule |
| M2 | Aug 9 | SRS + architecture design |
| M3 | Aug 30 | Auth, DB+RLS, UI skeleton, mid-eval (stub ML OK) |
| M4 | Oct 2 | Real CNN, Celery, alerts (through Progress Review 2) |
| M5 | Oct 3 | Testing doc, demo video, final report |

## Issue labels

`type: feature|bug|chore|docs|spike` · `area: api|web|mobile|ml|infra|db` · `priority: P0|P1|P2`

## Agent behaviour in this repo

- Match existing conventions before adding abstractions
- Minimize scope — smallest correct diff
- Do not commit unless the user asks
- Do not push to `main` — use feature branch + PR
- Link work to GitHub issues when creating tasks or PRs
